Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.72,0:00:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's May 1975, and Peter Gabriel has just played the last post on his oboe  
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.48,0:00:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,before he joins genesis on stage
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.78,0:00:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to perform The Lamb Lies Down on Broadway for the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.68,0:00:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Two months later, the band were writing and rehearsing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.73,0:00:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,new songs at their usual rehearsal studio,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.88,0:00:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the basement of the Una Billings School of Dance, in London's Shepherd's Bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.92,0:01:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In those initial sessions it was only Banks, Collins and Rutherford jamming together  
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.81,0:01:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with the basics of both Dance on a Volcano and Squonk
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.14,0:01:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,being written without Steve Hackett.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.24,0:01:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hackett was still putting the final touches to his own recording,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.34,0:01:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Voyage of the Acolyte together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.84,0:01:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd been recording this over June and July that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.04,0:01:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm writing the album throughout the whole of the lamb tour." ("I" refer to Hackett)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He claimed that the quiet, late-night writing sessions helped calm his onstage nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.92,0:01:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Much of the Acolyte album stands equal to the Lamb,  
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.20,0:01:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact the Acolyte's epic closer, {\i1}the Shadow of the Hierophant{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.27,0:01:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,had been co-written with Mike Rutherford.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.54,0:01:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was rehearsed by Genesis back in the Foxtrot days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.12,0:01:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tower Struck Down{\i} is another track that Hackett had also offered up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.23,0:02:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to his Genesis Band mates, only to have it rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whilst the band had managed to keep Gabriel's departure
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.31,0:02:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at closely guarded secrets up to this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.72,0:02:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,rumours of the singer's departure were
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,starting to circle it in the press over the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the 16th of August edition of Melody Maker, the secret was out:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.32,0:02:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabriel had left Genesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And soon after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.75,0:02:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Charisma Records received hundreds of audition tapes for the replacement singer. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.64,0:02:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,With many spelling doom for the band, they started recording
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.11,0:02:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in London's Trident Studios in October with the producer David Henschel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd previously been their assistant engineer since the days of Nursery Cryme.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.08,0:02:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point the band had no idea who would sing vocals on the new album
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.86,0:02:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or if indeed there would be vocals at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.46,0:02:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tony Banks has stated that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.63,0:02:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the album was never intended to be as vocal as it ultimately turned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this suggests that the band
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.40,0:03:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,may have been considering a more instrumental route.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.46,0:03:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you consider the popularity of jazz fusion
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.00,0:03:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and instrumental music in general at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,plus Collins' own involvement with Brand X, this is quite plausible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.88,0:03:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,During the recording sessions Gabriel himself visited them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.24,0:03:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and he commented to Melody Maker that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they had a much crisper and clearer sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.00,0:03:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the band sounded better than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, referred to their newfound speedy work rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.62,0:03:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trick of The Tail taking only one month to record
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to the four months for the Lamb. It does have something of a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.88,0:03:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire Trick of the Tail album was recorded instrumentally,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.39,0:03:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,before various singers were invited into the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.84,0:03:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,These prospective vocalists were asked to sing on
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.11,0:03:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,both Squonk and I Know What I Like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ultimately Collins's own singing of Squonk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.19,0:03:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that convinced the others that he was the right man for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.23,0:04:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's thought that up to 10 other singers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,were invited into Trident Studios to become the new Genesis frontman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.40,0:04:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,One of those was Bernie Frost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time he was the songwriting partner for Status Quo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.46,0:04:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd also played in various sessions with Phil Collins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're about to hear is an isolated vocal track from Bernie Frost,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,added into an instrumental version of a Genesis track, I'm sure you'll know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives an impression of how Bernie may have sounded
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.00,0:04:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,if he'd been chosen to be the Genesis frontman. Let's have a listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Another potential vocalist was singer Steve Gould from the band Rare Bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.67,0:05:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a group that had played many concerts with Genesis in the early 70s,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and were also on the Charisma Record label.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.52,0:05:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're about to hear next is another isolated vocal track
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.92,0:05:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from a Rare Bird song, {\i1}Sympathy{\i}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.80,0:05:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been added to a demo recording of Ripples.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.62,0:05:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It works to a degree and allowing us to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.97,0:05:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how Genesis could have sounded had he been chosen to be the vocalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly the results seem to me to be similar to that of Anthony Philips singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:05:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,See what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.80,0:06:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For the last of these recreations, we hear the ex-Hollies singer Alan Clarke singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.00,0:06:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Here this 1973 track, "People of a Kind", is mixed in with Squonk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's believed that Clarke was also a contender for the vacant singer position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.77,0:06:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,His name features on a list in a published Genesis biography.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.87,0:06:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, his vocal delivery holds up very well against the familiar Genesis track.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.00,0:07:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One can only imagine that his well-established position in the music industry  
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,may have deterred the band from ultimately considering him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.80,0:07:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The completed album was the first to feature individual songwriting credits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:07:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, for the first time, allowing listeners to know who wrote what formally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It leaves little doubts as to who the main songwriter in the band really was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is Tony Banks who receives a songwriting credit on each of the album's tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.44,0:08:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's now explore each of these tracks in depth,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.95,0:08:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and find out a little bit more about them...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the bulk of this song was written by Banks, Collins and Rutherford alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it's actually Steve Hackett who arguably provides the strongest moments on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.62,0:08:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That said Collins' drumming is also sensational here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a real measure of the song's status.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From its daunting opening to its thrilling freeform climax,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.00,0:08:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it leaves listeners in no doubt that the band are back and with a vengeance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.48,0:08:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a similar album opener to {\i1}Selling England{\i}'s "Dancing with the moonlight Knight".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And has to be one of the greatest songs that the band ever recorded,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.40,0:09:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and certainly the most important song that they ever made.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.77,0:09:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I think if this track had failed, and failed to grip you into this new album,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.47,0:09:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt you'd be watching this video now:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.64,0:09:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This gentle ballad provides the perfect calm after the previous storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.52,0:09:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The song was created from two existing tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.80,0:09:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The main intro and verse parts are from Steve Hackett.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.87,0:09:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're perfectly complemented by a chorus and ending from Banks,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.62,0:09:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who states that this was his favourite track on the album.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.55,0:09:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rare moment when the two band mates collaborated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.00,0:09:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,From here onwards, the relationship would begin to sour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.60,0:09:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As an aside, the track received a rare introduction by Steve Hackett
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.80,0:10:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before it was played at live concerts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.08,0:10:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Originally titled "Indians", Squonk's lyrics are based on a character and a book
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.27,0:10:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,called "Fearsome creatures in the slumber woods" by writer William Cox.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.80,0:10:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Squonk itself is a creature conscious of his ugly condition
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.57,0:10:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and he hides away in the Pennsylvanian forest as a consequence.  
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was this first song written for the album and it shows
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.12,0:10:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a band free of the burden of the Lamb, and Gabriel's often heavyweight lyrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the song is often thought to be about Gabriel himself.  
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.44,0:10:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The Squonk animal is also referenced in the Steely Dan song,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.27,0:10:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded two years prior to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And considering Rutherford's liking for Steely Dan though,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's probable that this is the influence of the song's title and subject matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.73,0:10:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bold and stomping Rutherford track  
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.34,0:11:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,reminiscent of Led Zeppelin's Kashmir and Levee Breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Next you'll hear an isolated drum track from The Levee Breaks
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.50,0:11:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with Collins singing on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.48,0:11:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There is something of a similarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.00,0:12:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This beautiful and often overlooked Tony Banks number
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,has a similar construction to what he would repeat on One for the Vine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.90,0:12:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It has an almost complete absence of Steve Hackett, 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.00,0:12:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's dominated by Banks as overlapping piano parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.46,0:12:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of only two tracks on the album that was never performed live.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.23,0:12:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's lyrics are astonishing in their sophistication and imagery  
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's perhaps another song about their recently departed singer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with its ideas of constantly yearning for pastures new.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil Collins have played the Artful Dodger as a teenager in a production of Oliver,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.40,0:13:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and here he reprises that role in his cockney best.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.00,0:13:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a comedy song that follows in the footsteps of the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.62,0:13:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Harold The Barrel, Get 'em Out by Friday and Epping Forest.  
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.08,0:13:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Essentially it's a Banks song, but it features some fantastic playing by the whole band.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.55,0:13:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's really co-writer Collins that makes this song vividly come to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The fifth song on the album is completely different
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.08,0:13:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in style and tone to everything that's perceiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.71,0:13:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, it shows that the band are more than capable of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.42,0:13:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,weathering the storm of Gabriel's departure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.16,0:14:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a beautiful Mike Rutherford ballad that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,pre-empts the more uncomplicated love songs that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.50,0:14:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that he especially would write over the 80s and 90s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.10,0:14:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was written with the express intention that Collins would sing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.51,0:14:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,similar to his cameo appearance on Selling England's More Fool Me,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.12,0:14:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The band played it live over many years, but it was perhaps most effectively played  
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in a poignant version on their 2007 reunion tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.26,0:14:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the second track on the album to be written exclusively by Tony Banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the lyrics are based on a neanderthal tribe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.60,0:14:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,found in William Golding's novel The Inheritors.  
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.00,0:14:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In a 1976 interview the band claimed that they were making a cartoon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.97,0:15:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to accompany this song, but it's failed to materialize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.86,0:15:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Banks have stated that the inspiration for this jaunty piano track  
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.16,0:15:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was the Beatles track Getting Better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.18,0:15:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The song was originally written in 1972 and intended for the Foxtrot album.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.88,0:15:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,One can imagine they're having a similar role to that of Willow Farm
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in Supper's Ready, as their introductions are quite similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.60,0:15:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A superb finale and one of the many examples of Genesis bookending an album  
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with musical themes from other tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This Collins inspired instrumental incorporates both elements of Squonk and Volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, hidden at the very end of the track,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.88,0:16:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Collins can be faintly heard saying the closing lines from Supper's Ready:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.61,0:16:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"There's an angel standing in the sun, free to get back home".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.80,0:16:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Collins has stated that the rhythmic nature of the track
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.41,0:16:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was inspired by the Santana track "Promise of a Fisherman".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.76,0:16:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The one notable outtake from the album is the track It's Yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.00,0:16:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was originally demoed during at Headley Grange during the Lamb writing sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.49,0:16:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And its lyrics and title seem to reference the narcissistic quality of Rael,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.11,0:16:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and one can easily imagine this track being used in the latter part of the Lamb album.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.67,0:16:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps replacing something like In The Rapids. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The track was ultimately issued as a b-side to the "Ripples" single,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:17:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and it includes a section that would be reused in Los Endos
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,before it ventures off into a pastoral soundscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's original title was "Beloved Summer"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it really suits that kind of ethereal quality of the of the latter sections.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.00,0:17:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been thought that the track would have been used also to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.11,0:17:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,link other songs together, most notably, Mad Man Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a similarity between the ending of it and the opening of Mad Man Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.72,0:17:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It segues very well into it. Let's have a listen see what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.16,0:18:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A Trick of the Tail was released on the 2nd of February 1976,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.70,0:18:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching number 3 in the UK charts and 31 in the US charts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.87,0:18:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These were both higher placings than the Lamb.  
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By June of that year, the album had sold a hundred thousand copies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.57,0:18:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,helping the band clear a substantial debt that they'd accrued during the Lamb tour.  
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.24,0:18:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The cover was created by artist Colin Elgie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.18,0:18:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,under the direction of the Hipgnosis design team.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an unusual step for Hipgnosis who usually created stark photographic pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This cover features an array of Victorian style line drawings,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.42,0:18:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,each depicting different characters from the songs.  
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.73,0:18:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderfully framed in a sepia tone cover
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.64,0:18:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that really complements the storybook nature of the album.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.23,0:18:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see here some mock covers based on other Colin Elgie drawings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.92,0:19:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The album was greeted by unanimous praise and the UK's leading music press.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.43,0:19:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chris Welsh of Melody Maker gave a glowing report
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,commenting that the overall production sound was better than ever.  
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.32,0:19:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The NME echoed this and also commented about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.77,0:19:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the album's immaculate production values.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.65,0:19:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And they observantly made reference to the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.37,0:19:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the band was starting to distance themselves from things likes Yes and ELP.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.71,0:19:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds paper gave it five stars and commented that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,although the band was starting to sound more commercial,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.13,0:19:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they hadn't sacrificed anything in terms of their musicianship or artistic credibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.52,0:19:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All three of these major music paper reviews reflect on a band
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.57,0:19:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that was full of reassured confidence that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.55,0:19:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,not only had they coped with Gabriel's departure, but they were better for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That seems to be the impression that comes across in the reviews at the time.  
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:19:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The band's next job was to take the album out on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.35,0:20:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,For this, the drummer Bill Bruford, who Phil had watched regularly
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.45,0:20:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in Yes's early days, was recruited as an on-stage drummer,  
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.28,0:20:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing Phil Collins to step up forward and sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.72,0:20:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Bruford's exemplary playing was a perfect foil for Collins
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.49,0:20:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the two combined brilliantly when playing together
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.13,0:20:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in shows with two drum kits on stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,something that became a Genesis standard from here on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.95,0:20:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The band had three rehearsal days in Pinewood Studios in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.47,0:20:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,before they jetted out for a Canadian and American tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.56,0:20:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the Canadian audience that first saw the band
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.24,0:20:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in their new incarnation on the 27th of March, 1976.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.64,0:20:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil Collins has admitted that on that gig his hands were trembling,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and he had a piece of paper on it with handwritten notes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.55,0:20:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what to say for the audience... How times changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.70,0:20:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The setlist combined old and new tracks, and for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.40,0:20:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced medleys into the band setlist, something that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that they would again increasingly include.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.32,0:20:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the most intriguing addition to the setlist
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.80,0:21:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,was the inclusion of the track White Mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.17,0:21:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which was from the Trespass album, something that Collins never even recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Overall it's an almost perfect album. Granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.29,0:21:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have the mystique and the atmosphere of maybe {\i1}Selling England{\i} or {\i1}Foxtrot{\i},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.71,0:21:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or the cinematic order and wonder of The Lamb,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps, it's not as brave and adventurous {\i1}as Nursery Cryme{\i} or {\i1}Trespass{\i},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but somehow this album seems to beat them all.  
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say it's my personal favourite,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but being objective, I've got to say this is their best.  
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you've enjoyed learning a bit more about it. I really enjoyed researching this.  
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As a lifelong Genesis fan, it's been intriguing to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.01,0:21:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,still discover new things about this band, so many years on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.74,0:21:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you have it - Genesis, A Trick of the Tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.72,0:00:35.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们回到1975年5月 Peter Gabriel在上台和Genesis进行
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.82,0:00:39.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最后一次Lamb专辑的演出之前 在排练时最后一次演奏了双簧管
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.14,0:00:44.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\c&H00FFFF&\pos(1594,478)}Peter Gabriel: Vocals
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.68,0:00:53.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,两个月之后 乐队在他们经常去的录音棚里 写新歌 并进行排练
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.88,0:00:58.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那个录音室是在伦敦 是这个舞蹈学校的地下室
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.35,0:01:10.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\c&H00FFFF&\pos(288,438)}Mike Rutherford: Bass
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:10.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\c&H00FFFF&\pos(954,300)}Phil Collins: Drums
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:10.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\c&H00FFFF&\pos(1654,752)}Tony Banks: Keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.92,0:01:06.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,刚开始排练的时候 只有Banks Collins Rutherford在一起围绕
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.81,0:01:10.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Dance on a Volcano和Squonk进行即兴创作
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.11,0:01:11.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这两首歌Steve Hackett在当时没有参与创作
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.82,0:01:20.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\c&H00FFFF&\pos(534,500)}Steve Hackett: Guitar
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.71,0:01:22.25,Comments,,0,0,0,,现在播放：Hands Of The Priestess by Steve Hackett
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.24,0:01:25.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Steve Hackett那时在完成录制他自己的专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.34,0:01:27.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是 The Voyage of the Acolyte
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.84,0:01:30.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1975的六月和七月 他一直在录制这张专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.04,0:01:33.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说他在Lamb专辑巡演途中 一直在写这张专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:39.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他还说 在后半夜安静的时候写歌 能帮他克服怯场
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.92,0:01:44.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很多Acolyte专辑里的歌质量能和Lamb媲美
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.20,0:01:48.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上 这张专辑史诗般的结尾曲 The Shadow of the Hierophant
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.27,0:01:50.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是他和Mike Rutherford一起写的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.54,0:01:53.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且在Genesis录制Foxtrot专辑的时候 他们就排练过了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.44,0:02:02.64,Comments,,0,0,0,,现在播放：Tower Struck Down by Steve Hackett
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.12,0:01:58.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Hackett还给他的Genesis队友提供了Tower Struck Down
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.69,0:02:00.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过被乐队否决了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:13.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然这时 乐队仍在严密保住Gabriel离队的秘密
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.72,0:02:15.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于乐队主唱Gabriel离队的传闻
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:18.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那个夏天一直在媒体中流传
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:23.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而在8月16日的Melody Maker杂志上 消息还是公开了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.32,0:02:25.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Gabriel已经离开了Genesis乐队
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:31.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在此之后 唱片公司收到很多想应聘歌手的试音带
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:31.07,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：唱片公司指Charisma Record，标志是《爱丽丝漫游仙境》里的Mad Hatter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.64,0:02:36.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在舆论普遍唱衰乐队的情况下 他们在十月入棚
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.11,0:02:41.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和制作人David Henschel一起录制新专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:45.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从录制Nursery Cryme开始 他就是助理录音工程师了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.08,0:02:50.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这时 乐队还没想好由谁来唱这张新专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.86,0:02:53.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者说 这张专辑是否需要包括人声
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.46,0:02:59.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Tony Banks说过 这张专辑从来没有打算像成品那样 录进人声
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:03.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这暗示了 当时乐队曾经考虑过纯音乐方向
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.46,0:03:09.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时融合爵士乐和纯器乐作品十分流行
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:14.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,加上Collins也加入了融合爵士乐队Brand X 这么想应该没错
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.88,0:03:20.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在录音的时候 Gabriel亲自拜访了他们
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.24,0:03:27.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他向Melody Maker说 他们的声音更加清脆 比之前的更好了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:30.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里 我提一下他们全新的工作节奏 相当高效
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.62,0:03:33.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相较于上一张专辑四个月的录制时间
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:36.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们这回只花了一个月就录好了 确实有点能力哈
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.88,0:03:43.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在很多的歌手到录音室应聘歌手之前
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.39,0:03:46.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这张专辑的器乐部分就已经录好了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.84,0:03:52.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,应聘主唱的人被要求歌唱Sqounk和I Know What I Like
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:56.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,结果Collins唱的Squonk十分合适
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.19,0:03:58.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这说服了其他队友 他们觉得Phil是当主唱的最合适人选
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.23,0:04:01.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,话说回来 据说当时最多有10个歌手应邀来到
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:06.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,录音室 来应聘Genesis的主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.40,0:04:09.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其中一个是Bernie Frost
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:12.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这时 他是Status Quo的创作伙伴
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.46,0:04:15.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他和Phil Collins也在一起录过几次音
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:19.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你接下来将听到的 是Bernie Frost演唱过的一首歌与
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:24.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Genesis某首歌的器乐相结合 这首歌各位应该很熟悉
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得如果Bernie真成了Genesis主唱的话
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.00,0:04:31.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就会是这样了吧 我们来听听吧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.73,0:05:24.50,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：不熟悉的话，器乐部分来自Mad Man Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:29.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,另一个潜在的主唱选择是Rare Bird的主唱Steve Gould
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.67,0:05:33.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在七十年代早期 他们和Genesis乐队在一起演出过很多次
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:36.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且都签在了同一家唱片公司
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.52,0:05:42.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接下来要听到的 是一首由Rare Bird演奏的歌曲 Sympathy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.80,0:05:45.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的人声叠录在早期Ripples的录音小样中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.62,0:05:47.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样做 在某种程度上 让我们一瞥
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.97,0:05:52.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果他被选为Genesis主唱的话 会是什么样
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:56.32,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：Anthony Philips是Genesis原先的吉他手 由于怯场而离队
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:56.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看上去更像是Anthony Philips唱歌的感觉
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:05:57.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们听听看
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.80,0:06:38.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有最后一个要还原的 这位是前Hollies乐队的主唱Alan Clarke
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.00,0:06:43.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他在1973演唱的People of a Kind将会叠录在Squonk器乐之上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:47.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时普遍认为Clarke也是主唱的人选
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.77,0:06:51.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的名字出现在Genesis传记里的一张名单上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.87,0:06:56.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,显然 他的声色能和大家熟知的Genesis歌曲配合得很好
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.00,0:07:00.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可想而知 因为他在音乐界的地位很高
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:03.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以乐队最终没有选择他当主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.80,0:07:54.00,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：在此之前，署名只有"Genesis"，而Pound专辑的署名是"全员创作所有歌曲"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.80,0:07:49.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这张专辑中 他们第一次写上了每一首歌的署名
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:07:54.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,听众们可以头一回正式知道每首歌的具体作者了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:57.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过这也留下了一点困惑 谁到底是乐队的主要创作者
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:02.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟Tony Banks在专辑里的每首歌都有署名
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.44,0:08:07.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们深入探索 找出更多吧
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:23.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管这首歌的大部分都是由Banks Collins和Rutherford编写的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:27.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但显然 Steve Hackett编写了这首歌中最带劲的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.62,0:08:31.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然 Collins的鼓声也很令人印象深刻
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:34.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这很好体现出了这首歌给人的感觉
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:38.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌开场激扬人心 变化自由多样 力度十足
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.00,0:08:42.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很明显乐队带着一腔复仇的欲望 回归到大众的视野
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.48,0:08:58.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,专辑开头和Pound专辑的开幕曲很相似
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:05.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以说是这个乐队最伟大 最重要的一首歌
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.77,0:09:10.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要是这首歌失败了 没有吸引你继续听这个新专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.47,0:09:12.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,估计你也不会点进这个视频
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.64,0:09:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在上一首风云变幻之后 这首平静的民谣让听众平静了下来
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.52,0:09:38.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌由两首歌拼接而成
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.80,0:09:41.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,引子和主歌部分是Steve Hackett写的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.87,0:09:45.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在此基础上 Banks写的副歌和结尾完美补全了这首歌
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.62,0:09:48.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Banks说在这张专辑里 他最喜欢这首歌
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.55,0:09:52.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这俩人能合作 还挺少见了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.00,0:09:55.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟到后面 他们俩关系变差了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.60,0:10:02.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,另说一句 在现场演出前 Steve Hackett会介绍一两句
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.08,0:10:19.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Sqounk原先叫做Indians 而歌词是从William Cox写的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.27,0:10:23.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Fearsome creatures in the slumber woods上面的主角和情节取材
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.80,0:10:27.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Squonk这个生物很在意自己丑陋的外表
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.57,0:10:31.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此 他在宾夕法尼亚的森林里隐居
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:34.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是乐队为这张专辑写的第一首歌 体现了他们
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.12,0:10:38.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从Lamb专辑的影响和Gabriel晦涩的歌词中解放出来
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:42.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上 大家普遍认为这首歌内容是关于Gabriel的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.44,0:10:48.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这首歌录制两年前 Squonk就在Steely Dan写的一首歌中出现了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:51.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,考虑到Rutherford喜欢Steedy Dan
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:56.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许就是那首歌影响了这首歌的题目和主题
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.73,0:10:59.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌由Rutherford编曲 节奏强烈 血气方刚
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.34,0:11:03.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让人联想到Led Zeppelin的Kashmir和Levee Breaks
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:09.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接下来你将听到Collins随着Levee Breaks的鼓声唱歌
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:09.48,Comments,,0,0,0,,SuperBart: Bonzo yyds!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.48,0:11:11.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,显然这两者有些相似之处
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.00,0:12:07.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首优美的歌由Tony Banks编写 经常被忽视
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:11.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌的结构和他将在One for the Vine里体现的很相似
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:11.90,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：Genesis - Wind & Wuthering - One for the Vine\N这张专辑我强烈推荐:-D
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.90,0:12:15.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌完全没有Hackett的参与
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.00,0:12:18.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由Banks的重叠的钢琴音符所主导
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.46,0:12:23.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,整张专辑有两首歌从来没有现场演出过 这个是其中之一
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.23,0:12:27.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌歌词十分精致 想象力十足 十分有水平
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:31.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,兴许又是一首关于离队主唱Gabriel的歌曲
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:35.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟歌词大意是要寻找一片新的天地
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:35.08,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：pastures指一片由青草覆盖的土地
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:04.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Collins小时候 曾经在Oliver剧中演过Artful Dodger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:04.40,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：Artful Dodger是雾都孤儿里面的扒手
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.40,0:13:08.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他在这首歌中 又一次在伦敦东城客串了这位
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.00,0:13:14.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌充满幽默气息 之前专辑里面也有类似的歌
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.00,0:13:14.00,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：Harold The Barrel from Nursery Cryme\NGet 'em Out by Friday from Foxtrot\NThe Battle of Epping Forest from Selling England by the Pound
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.08,0:13:16.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本质上 这是首Banks的歌曲
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.60,0:13:19.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但乐队全体成员在这首歌中都有出色表现
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.55,0:13:23.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但让这首歌栩栩如生的 还得是协作者Phil Collins
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:29.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它表现出来的风格和音调 和前面歌的完全不同
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.71,0:13:34.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然 这也体现了他们确实经受住了Gabriel离队的冲击
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.16,0:14:04.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首由Mike Rutherford写的民谣预示了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:10.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他将在八十年代和九十年代写很多的口水歌
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.10,0:14:14.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌写出来 就是为了让Collins唱
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.51,0:14:18.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有点像Selling England里面的小调More Fool Me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.12,0:14:23.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,乐队在现场表演过很多回 但在2007年重聚演唱会上
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:27.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们经常演奏一个更凄美的版本
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:27.84,Comments,,0,0,0,,SuperBart：我的童年像小鸟一样不回来:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.26,0:14:45.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是这张专辑中 第二首由Tony Banks独立写出来的歌
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:48.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,歌词则是改编自William Golding写的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.60,0:14:52.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,小说The Inheritors里的尼安德特部落
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.00,0:14:56.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在一次1976年的访谈中 乐队说他们想为每首歌
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.97,0:15:00.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,画一张漫画 不过最终没有实现
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.86,0:15:06.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Banks说歌曲中轻快的钢琴声 受到了Beatles的Getting Better影响
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.18,0:15:11.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌原写于1972年 本来是为了Foxtrot专辑准备的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.88,0:15:15.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,真要放进Foxtrot专辑的话 那就是Supper Ready里面的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:18.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Willow Farm部分 毕竟引入部分十分相似
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.88,0:15:18.70,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：Willow Farm部分在Supper's Ready里的10分钟到15分钟
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.60,0:15:52.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,十分漂亮的结尾曲 串烧了这张专辑里的其他歌曲
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:58.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Collins从Sqounk和Volcano两首歌中提取元素 并放在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:05.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有 在歌曲的结尾 Collins在小声地唱Supper's Ready的最后一句
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.61,0:16:09.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,"天使沐浴在阳光下 自由地回家去了"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.80,0:16:16.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Collins说 这首歌的节奏本源是Santana的Promise of a Fisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.76,0:16:34.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有一首值得注意的It's Yourself 录好了但没有收进专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.00,0:16:38.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原先是在Headley Grange写Lamb专辑期间 录制的小样
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.49,0:16:44.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,歌词和题目看上去和Rael的自恋有关
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.49,0:16:44.11,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：Rael是Lamb专辑里，故事的主人公
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.11,0:16:48.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很容易联想到 这首歌可以用在Lamb专辑的后面
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.67,0:16:51.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能替代In The Rapids那首歌
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:56.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌最终给Ripples歌曲单曲做B面了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:17:00.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,歌曲里面有一段 最终用在了Los Endos里面
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:03.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就在后面进入田园意像之前的过渡部分之前
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:07.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本来是叫"Beloved Summer"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:13.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,确实挺适合那张专辑后面的气氛
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.00,0:17:16.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有人认为这首歌的某些部分在其他歌曲中
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.11,0:17:20.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也出现了 最明显的是Mad Man Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:24.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这首歌的结尾部分和Mad Man Moon开头有相似之处
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.72,0:17:28.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这两首歌过渡得非常自然 来感受一下吧
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.16,0:18:08.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,A Trick of the Tail发行于1976年2月2日
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.70,0:18:13.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,冲到了英国排行榜第三 美国排行榜第三十一名
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.87,0:18:16.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,排名都比Lamb专辑高
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:20.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到了那年六月 专辑已经售出了超过十万份
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.57,0:18:25.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,帮助乐队还清了在Lamb专辑巡演期间欠下的大量债务
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.24,0:18:36.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,封面由Colin Elgie在Hipgnosis设计组指导下绘制
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:41.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于经常创作拍摄作品的Hipgnosis来说 这回很不寻常
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:41.71,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：各位可以去看看Wish You Were Here的封面，那些都是拍的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:45.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,封面则是一系列维多利亚时代风格的白描画
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.42,0:18:48.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每一个人物都对应着专辑里的歌曲
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.73,0:18:51.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些画衬托在棕褐色的纸上
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.64,0:18:55.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,完美体现了这张专辑的故事性
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.23,0:18:59.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以看看这些根据Colin Elgie画风绘制的封面
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.92,0:19:08.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这张专辑获得了英国主要音乐媒体的一致好评
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.43,0:19:11.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Melody Maker杂志的Chris Welsh对这张专辑赞不绝口
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:15.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,评论说这张专辑的总体声效制作 比之前的要好
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.32,0:19:20.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,NME杂志也这么说 还评论说这张专辑完美的制作水平
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.65,0:19:23.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们还敏锐地提到了一个事实
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.37,0:19:27.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,乐队正在将风格从诸如Yes和ELP那样的转变开来
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.71,0:19:30.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Sounds Paper给了个五星好评 评论说
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:33.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管整个乐队开始偏商业化了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.13,0:19:37.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在音乐和创造力方面 他没有任何妥协
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.52,0:19:45.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这三个主要报纸的评论体现了乐队充满着信心和勇气
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.55,0:19:49.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们不仅克服了Gabriel离队的影响 而且更加成功了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:53.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在当时评论看来 这确实挺让人印象深刻
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:19:58.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,乐队的下一个人任务 就是带着专辑去巡演
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.35,0:20:01.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了巡演 Yes早期的鼓手Bill Bruford
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.45,0:20:05.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被雇进来当现场鼓手 Phil早年经常去看他演出
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.28,0:20:08.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样Phil就可以站在观众面前唱歌了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.72,0:20:12.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Bruford教科书般的演奏 足以和Collins相衬托
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.72,0:20:12.49,Comments,,0,0,0,,SuperBart：毕竟是Robert Fripp看上的人
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:10.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\c&H00FFFF&\pos(1658,612)}Bill Bruford: Drums
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.49,0:20:17.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们俩台上演奏两个鼓 配合得十分漂亮
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:20.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个以后也成了Genesis演唱会的某种标配了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.95,0:20:25.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在去加拿大和美国巡演之前
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.47,0:20:28.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们在英国的Pinewood Studios排练了三天
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.56,0:20:31.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1976年3月27日 加拿大的乐迷们第一次看到
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.24,0:20:35.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这支脱胎换骨的乐队
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.64,0:20:39.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Phil Collins承认过 在那个现场上 他的手在哆嗦
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:44.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了记一些给观众的话 他自己写了个便条 时光如梭啊
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.70,0:20:50.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,节目单上有老歌 也有新歌 而且头一回
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.40,0:20:55.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将组曲写进了节目单 他们之后也会经常这么做
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.32,0:21:00.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许节目单上最耐人寻味的一首歌 就是这首White Mountain了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.17,0:21:03.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是Trespass上的歌 Collins没有参与录制
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:15.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,总体来说 这个专辑接近完美
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.29,0:21:19.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它没有Selling England或Foxtrot那样的神秘气氛
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.29,0:21:19.71,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：这两张专辑的歌词，要没人解释，我看不明白:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.71,0:21:23.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者The Lamb那样的戏剧性和想象力
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.71,0:21:23.68,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：我听了三遍，都不知道这张专辑讲了什么故事:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:28.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者说 没有Nursery Cryme和Trespass那样的勇敢冒险属性
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:28.97,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：这两张专辑里的歌，都是一个一个小故事，不过Musical Box很怪诞\NTrespass听上去很舒服呢:-)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:31.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但不知为何 这张专辑能把它们都给比下去
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:34.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不会说这是我个人的最爱
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:37.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但客观地说 这张专辑是他们的最佳
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:44.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,希望大家喜欢看 从中知道更多知识 查资料的时候我很享受
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:48.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为终生的Genesis粉丝 这么多年来
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.01,0:21:51.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还能探索到到乐队的新东西 好奇妙呢
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.74,0:21:54.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好啦 Genesis的A Trick of the Tail就给大家介绍到这里了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.75,0:21:43.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\c&H00FFFF&\pos(276,758)}Tony Banks: Keyboard
